						<summary>

						<p>On the outer <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> of the Mantrapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Perumā[ḷ*] ••• dēva year: 14.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged epigraph may be assigned to c. 13th century on palaeographical grounds.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record an order <hi rend="italic">(ōlai)</hi> issued by a certain [Śō]ḻiyavaraiyaṉ.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record some grant of land made to the temple of Tiruvuśāttāṉam-uḍaiyār. This order was attested by the <hi rend="italic">[ūravar]</hi> of Koṅgaṇakkuḍi and the <hi rend="italic">kāraṇavar</hi> of Kāḍandaikkuḍi. Besides these, a number of others such as the <hi rend="italic">nāṭṭavar</hi> of Ālattūr, are also referred to have signed this document. Since some of the signatories of this order figure in a record dated in the 13th+1st year of the reign of Chaḍaiyavarmaṉ Sundara-pāṇḍya, the present inscription may also be assigned to the king mentioned above (<hi rend="italic">A.R.Ep.,</hi> 1908, No. 226).</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
